uk.co.strangeskies.modabi.impl.schema.utilities

Class HidingChildrenConfigurator

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.co.strangeskies.modabi.impl.schema.utilities.HidingChildrenConfigurator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ChildrenConfigurator, uk.co.strangeskies.utilities.factory.Factory<ChildrenContainer>

    public class HidingChildrenConfigurator
extends Object
implements ChildrenConfigurator
    Children, both inherited and then subsequently added, are merged with sequence ordering preservation, with higher priority children placed earlier. Nodes added through this configurator are merged into the inherited children with highest priority, so will appear as early as possible in the ultimate effective sequence. Ordering preservation means, for example, we cannot inherit both sequences ["a", "b"] and ["b", "a"], as it is not possible to merge the nodes and preserve ordering. Early priority means, for example, that merging the sequence ["a", "b", "c", "d"] with the lower priority sequence ["1", "a", "2", "3", "c", "4"] will result in the sequence ["1", "a", "b", "2", "3", "c", "d", "4"], as higher priority sequences are prioritised for earlier placement wherever compatible with sequence ordering preservation.
